    "show_notes_html": "<h3>The Valve Wire Weekly - 2026-04-11</h3>\n<p><strong>Duration:</strong> 23:06 | <strong>Hosts:</strong> E. Nolan Beckett, MD &amp; Claire Marchand, MBA</p>\n<h4>Timestamps</h4><ul>\n<li>[00:52] Introduction</li>\n<li>[01:53] Disclaimer</li>\n<li>[02:10] Top Stories</li>\n<li>[06:58] Aortic Valve (TAVR/TAVI)</li>\n<li>[10:50] Mitral Valve (Repair & Replacement)</li>\n<li>[13:09] Tricuspid Valve (Repair & Replacement)</li>\n<li>[14:42] Clinical Trials Update</li>\n<li>[16:26] Surgical vs. Transcatheter</li>\n<li>[18:13] Market & Industry</li>\n<li>[20:52] Closing Thoughts</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Summary</h4><p>Welcome to The Valve Wire Weekly. I&#x27;m Nolan Beckett, and this is episode one \u2014 a show we&#x27;ve been wanting to launch for a long time. Joining me as always is Claire Marchand. Claire, we picked quite a week to start. We really did, Nolan. CMS just opened what could be the most consequential TAVR regulatory review in years, the tricuspid replacement space exploded with three major milestones in a single week, and we&#x27;ve got new TAVR competitors entering randomized trials. There&#x27;s a lot to unpack. So here&#x27;s what&#x27;s coming: we&#x27;ll lead with the CMS National Coverage Analysis for TAVR, then dive into the tricuspid valve replacement race, a really provocative study stress-testing the new ESC tricuspid guidelines against real-world data, and new entrants challenging Edwards Lifesciences and Medtronic in the TAVR space. Then we&#x27;ll hit aortic, mitral, tricuspid findings, clinical trials, and Claire will walk us through a market that is under serious pressure heading into earnings season.</p>\n<h4>Articles &amp; Sources</h4><ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://news.google.?oc=5&amp;hl=en-US&amp;gl=US&amp;ceid=US:en\">reconsideration of the national coverage determination for TAVR (CAG-00430R2)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMitgFBVV95cUxOenZIQkZGQWlKX25GWjF2TW81UjAyM054NkVmdzE4TFNMQ2xTTVZWW